#: ../../inarticulations.rst:5
msgid "Spoken inarticulations"
msgstr "話される非分節音"

#: ../../inarticulations.rst:7
msgid ""
"Words such as ‘mumble’, ‘sigh’, and ‘groan’ are spoken in places where their"
" referent might more naturally be used. It has been suggested that this "
"usage derives from the impossibility of representing such noises on a comm "
"link or in electronic mail, MUDs, and IRC channels (interestingly, the same "
"sorts of constructions have been showing up with increasing frequency in "
"comic strips). Another expression sometimes heard is \"Complain! \", meaning"
" \"I have a complaint!\""
msgstr ""
"‘mumble’、‘sigh’、‘groan’といった語が、その指示対象がより自然に使われそうな場所で口にされる。この用法は、そうした音を通信回線や電子メール、MUD、IRCチャンネル上で表現することが不可能なことに由来すると示唆されている(興味深いことに、同じ種類の構成が漫画にもますます高い頻度で現れている)。時に聞かれるもう一つの表現は「Complain!」で、「I"
" have a complaint!(文句がある!)」を意味する。"
